{"title_page": "Dakota Daulby", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|{{Primary sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{Unreliable sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{BLP IMDb refimprove|date=January 2020}}}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Dakota Daulby\n| image       =\n| image_size  = 150px\n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1994|10|10|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vancouver, British Columbia|Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]\n| yearsactive = 2010\u2013present\n| occupation  = Actor, Director, Producer, Writer\n| website = {{URL|www.dakotadaulby.com}}\n}}\n'''Dakota Daulby''' (born October 10, 1994) is a Canadian film and television actor, producer, director and screenwriter.\n\n==Early life==\nDaulby was born in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]].<ref name=\"Arts: Maple Ridge Actor Dakota Daulby Stars In The Woodcarver\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.pittmeadowstoday.ca/arts-maple-ridge-actor-dakota-daulby-stars-in-the-woodcarver/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-07-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714205208/http://www.pittmeadowstoday.ca/arts-maple-ridge-actor-dakota-daulby-stars-in-the-woodcarver/ |archive-date=2014-07-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He spends his time between his home town of [[Maple Ridge, British Columbia|Maple Ridge]] and [[Vancouver]].<ref name=\"Arts: Maple Ridge Actor Dakota Daulby Stars In The Woodcarver\"/> He started his two-year acting program under the department head and [[Gemini Award]] winning actor Phil Granger and completed the program with honours in September 2014.<ref name=\"scenecreek.com\">[http://scenecreek.com/interviews/dakota-daulby-talks-career-falling-skies/ Interview: Dakota Daulby talks about his career and Falling Skies]</ref><ref>[http://thepermanentrainpress.com/post/90704821516 The Permanent Rain Press Interview With Dakota Daulby]</ref>\n\n==Career==\nDaulby entered the American market with work on TV shows such as ''[[Falling Skies]]'' and ''[[Wayward Pines]]''. He discovered his love for acting at a young age and proceeded to enroll in [[New Image College]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newimage.ca/|title=Acting and Esthetician School, Makeup Artist Training and Workshops|website=New Image College|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref> \n\n=== ''2011 - 2014: early roles'' ===\n\nDaulby got his first break after landing the lead role in the award-winning short film ''Why Does God Hate Me?'', written and directed by [[Joel Ashton McCarthy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://joelmccarthy.com/|title=Video on Joel Ashton McCarthy|website=Joel Ashton McCarthy|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref> The film was featured at the [[New York Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmlinc.org/nyff2016/|title=54th New York Film Festival|newspaper=Film Society of Lincoln Center|access-date=2017-02-16|language=en-US}}</ref> and other film festivals across the world.<ref name=\"scenecreek.com\" /><ref name=\"Dakota Daulby\">https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4464492/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm</ref>\n\nDaulby next appeared in the [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] film ''[[Girl Fight]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1956502/|title=Girl Fight IMDB|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> by director [[Stephen Gyllenhaal]]. He cited Gyllenhaal's son, [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] as a major influence on his career.\n\nThe following year, Daulby landed the starring role in the feature film ''The Woodcarver'', alongside [[John Ratzenberger]].<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20140714153854/http://www.montrealgazette.com/entertainment/movie-guide/story.html?id=9981150]</ref><ref name=\"Teen thespian forging name for himself\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20140714120156/http://www.mrtimes.com/news/teen-thespian-forging-name-for-himself-1.490722]</ref> He co-starred as the love interest in the [[Leo Award]]-winning big screen adaptation ''[[Sitting on the Edge of Marlene]]'' alongside [[Paloma Kwiatkowski]] and [[Suzanne Cl\u00e9ment]], adapted from the novella ''The Trouble With Marlene'' by [[Billie Livingston]].<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\" /><ref name=\"VANCOUVER ACTOR DAKOTA DAULBY TAKES ON TOUGH ROLE IN SPIELBERG SERIES\">http://www.vancitybuzz.com/2014/06/vancouver-actor-dakota-daulby-takes-tough-role-spielberg-series/</ref>\n\n=== ''2014 - : Falling Skies'' ===\n\nDaulby appeared in the series ''[[Spooksville]]'', [[The CW|CW's]] [[IZombie (TV series)|''iZombie'']], ''Pretty Little Addict'' and in a recurring role on the fourth season of ''[[Falling Skies]]''.<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\" /><ref name=\"FALLING SKIES Scoop: Dakota Daulby Talks Reeducation Camps and Humanity\u2019s Survival in Season 4\">http://www.thetvaddict.com/2014/06/22/falling-skies-scoop-dakota-daulby-talks-reeducation-camps-and-humanitys-survival-in-season-4/</ref><ref name=\"Dakota Daulby Discusses His Role on Falling Skies\">{{cite web |url=http://thetelevixen.com/2014/06/dakota-daulby-discusses-his-role-on-falling-skies/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-05 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714133820/http://thetelevixen.com/2014/06/dakota-daulby-discusses-his-role-on-falling-skies/ |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref> Daulby portrays the ruthless Nazi-esque head of the Espheni brainwashing camps, Kent Matthews. On the show, he worked closely with [[Maxim Knight]], [[Noah Wyle]], [[Will Patton]], [[Doug Jones (actor)|Doug Jones]] and [[Colin Cunningham]].<ref name=\"INTERVIEW: Dakota Daulby on FALLING SKIES, BLACK FLY & SITTING ON THE EDGE OF MARLENE\">http://yvrshoots.com/2014/06/interview-dakota-daulby-on-falling-skies-black-fly-sitting-on-the-edge-of-marlene.html#.U7eBgePZ-6x</ref>\n\nIn early 2014, Daulby won the leading role in the Canadian horror thriller, ''Black Fly'', which was released at international film festivals in 2015.<ref name=\"INTERVIEW: Dakota Daulby on FALLING SKIES, BLACK FLY & SITTING ON THE EDGE OF MARLENE\" /><ref name=\"Dakota Daulby: Today's Notable Young Professional\">{{cite web |url=http://notable.ca/nationwide/young-professionals/Dakota-Daulby-Todays-Notable-Young-Professional/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-05 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707084202/http://notable.ca/nationwide/young-professionals/Dakota-Daulby-Todays-Notable-Young-Professional/ |archivedate=2014-07-07 |df= }}</ref> Daulby received a nomination at Leo Awards for \"Best Male Lead in a Motion Picture\" - losing to his Black Fly co-star Matthew MacCaull. In November 2015, Daulby was nominated for and won the [[ACTRA]] Union of BC Performers (UBCP) award for the best emerging performer for his role in ''Black Fly''.\n\nDaulby co-wrote, co-directed, and co-produced over 20 short and alternative media films with [[New Image College|New Image Entertainment]].<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\" /><ref name=\"Camille Sullivan and Michael Eklund bag the big prizes at UBCP/ATRA 2015 awards\">https://www.straight.com/blogra/573801/camille-sullivan-and-michael-eklund-bag-big-prizes-ubcpactra-awards</ref> In 2016, he had a guest starring role opposite Academy Award nominatee [[Djimon Hounsou]], in [[M. Night Shyamalan]]'s ''[[Wayward Pines]]''.<ref name=\"ACTOR DAKOTA DAULBY TALKS 'WAYWARD PINES' AND M. NIGHT SHYAMALAN\">https://thehudsucker.com/2016/07/06/actor-dakota-daulby-talks-wayward-pines-and-m-night-shyamalan/</ref> Daulby played Travis in the [[Luc Besson]] fantasy epic, [[Warrior's Gate]].<ref name=\"seat42f\">{{cite web|url=http://www.seat42f.com/exclusive-wayward-pines-scoop-shining-the-spotlight-on-dakota-daulby.html|access-date=2017-01-30|date=2016-07-05|title=EXCLUSIVE: WAYWARD PINES Scoop: Shining the Spotlight on Dakota Daulby|first1=Tiffany|last1=Vogt|website=seat42f.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Other projects ===\n\nDaulby was the co-creator of the Vancouver-based 72 horror film festival, The Phrike Filmfest - also acting as the shows official MC. He is highly involved in New Image College's community events, he hosted and appeared on such shows like ''[[Breakfast Television]]'', the Fair at the PNE, [[EP Daily|Electric Playground]] and Shaw Television.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Camp Goodtimes''\n| Max\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Why Does God Hate Me?''\n| Matthew\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Girl Fight]]''\n| Sophomore Boy #1 \n| TV Movie\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''The Woodcarver''\n| Matthew\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Mimi & Me''\n| Sam Vaughn\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Spooksville (TV series)|Spooksville]]''\n| Jerome Simone; 1 episode\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Falling Skies]]''\n| Kent Matthews; 5 episodes\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Sitting on the Edge of Marlene]]''\n| Drew\n| Movie\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Roar''\n| Josh\n| Short Film<br>Nominated {{ndash}} [[Leo Award]] for Best Lead Performance by a Male in a Short Drama<ref name=leofifteen />\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Black Fly''\n| Jake Henson\n| Movie<br>Nominated {{ndash}} [[Leo Award]] for Best Lead Performance by a Male in a Motion Picture<ref name=leofifteen>{{cite web|title=2015 nominees|url=http://www.leoawards.com/past_winners/pdf/2015.pdf|website=leoawards.com|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref><br>Nominated {{ndash}} [[ACTRA Awards|UBCP/ACTRA Award]] for Best Newcomer<ref>{{cite web|title=UBCP/ACTRA  \u2013  The 2015 UBCP/ACTRA AWARDS NOMINEES ANNOUNCED|url=http://www.ubcp.com/press-releases/2015/09/the-2015-ubcpactra-awards-nominees-announced/|website=www.ubcp.com|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref> \n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Josh & Tom''\n| Tom; co-producer\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''That Strawberry?''\n| Co-writer, co-director, and co-producer\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[iZombie (TV series)|iZombie]]''\n| Tommy/Tom; 2 episodes\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Pretty Little Addict''\n| Tyler Kinan\n| TV Movie\n|- \n| 2016\n| ''[[Warrior's Gate]]''\n| Travis\n| Movie\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Wayward Pines (TV series)|Wayward Pines]]''\n| Griffin; 1 episode\n| TV Series<br>Nominated {{ndash}} [[Leo Award]] for Best Guest Performance by a Male in a Dramatic Series<ref>{{cite web|title=Leo Awards, Nominees by Name 2017|url=http://www.leoawards.com/2017/nominees/by_name.php|website=www.leoawards.com|accessdate=2 May 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170527200921/http://www.leoawards.com/2017/nominees/by_name.php|archivedate=27 May 2017|df=}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|[[The 100 (TV series)|The 100]]\n|Sheidheda/ Dark Commander\n|TV Series\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daulby, Dakota}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Vancouver]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|{{Primary sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{Unreliable sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{BLP IMDb refimprove|date=January 2020}}}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Dakota Daulby\n| image       =\n| image_size  = 150px\n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1994|10|10|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vancouver, British Columbia|Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]\n| yearsactive = 2010\u2013present\n| occupation  = Actor, Director, Producer, Writer\n| website = {{URL|www.dakotadaulby.com}}\n}}\n'''Dakota Daulby''' (born October 10, 1994) is a Canadian film and television actor, producer, director and screenwriter.\n\n==Early life==\nDaulby was born in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]].<ref name=\"Arts: Maple Ridge Actor Dakota Daulby Stars In The Woodcarver\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.pittmeadowstoday.ca/arts-maple-ridge-actor-dakota-daulby-stars-in-the-woodcarver/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-07-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714205208/http://www.pittmeadowstoday.ca/arts-maple-ridge-actor-dakota-daulby-stars-in-the-woodcarver/ |archive-date=2014-07-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He spends his time between his home town of [[Maple Ridge, British Columbia|Maple Ridge]] and [[Vancouver]].<ref name=\"Arts: Maple Ridge Actor Dakota Daulby Stars In The Woodcarver\"/> He started his two-year acting program under the department head and [[Gemini Award]] winning actor Phil Granger and completed the program with honours in September 2014.<ref name=\"scenecreek.com\">[http://scenecreek.com/interviews/dakota-daulby-talks-career-falling-skies/ Interview: Dakota Daulby talks about his career and Falling Skies]</ref><ref>[http://thepermanentrainpress.com/post/90704821516 The Permanent Rain Press Interview With Dakota Daulby]</ref>\n\n==Career==\nDaulby entered the American market with work on TV shows such as ''[[Falling Skies]]'' and ''[[Wayward Pines]]''. He discovered his love for acting at a young age and proceeded to enroll in [[New Image College]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newimage.ca/|title=Acting and Esthetician School, Makeup Artist Training and Workshops|website=New Image College|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref> \n\n=== ''2011 - 2014: early roles'' ===\n\nDaulby got his first break after landing the lead role in the award-winning short film ''Why Does God Hate Me?'', written and directed by [[Joel Ashton McCarthy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://joelmccarthy.com/|title=Video on Joel Ashton McCarthy|website=Joel Ashton McCarthy|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref> The film was featured at the [[New York Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmlinc.org/nyff2016/|title=54th New York Film Festival|newspaper=Film Society of Lincoln Center|access-date=2017-02-16|language=en-US}}</ref> an other film festivals across the world.<ref name=\"scenecreek.com\" /><ref name=\"Dakota Daulby\">https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4464492/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm</ref>\n\nDaulby next appeared in the [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] film ''[[Girl Fight]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1956502/|title=Girl Fight IMDB|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> by director [[Stephen Gyllenhaal]]. He cited Gyllenhaal's son, [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] as a major influence on his career.\n\nThe following year, Daulby landed the starring role in the feature film ''The Woodcarver'', alongside [[John Ratzenberger]].<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20140714153854/http://www.montrealgazette.com/entertainment/movie-guide/story.html?id=9981150]</ref><ref name=\"Teen thespian forging name for himself\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20140714120156/http://www.mrtimes.com/news/teen-thespian-forging-name-for-himself-1.490722]</ref> He co-starred as the love interest in the [[Leo Award]]-winning big screen adaptation ''[[Sitting on the Edge of Marlene]]'' alongside [[Paloma Kwiatkowski]] and [[Suzanne Cl\u00e9ment]], adapted from the novella ''The Trouble With Marlene'' by [[Billie Livingston]].<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\" /><ref name=\"VANCOUVER ACTOR DAKOTA DAULBY TAKES ON TOUGH ROLE IN SPIELBERG SERIES\">http://www.vancitybuzz.com/2014/06/vancouver-actor-dakota-daulby-takes-tough-role-spielberg-series/</ref>\n\n=== ''2014 - : Falling Skies'' ===\n\nDaulby appeared in the series ''[[Spooksville]]'', [[The CW|CW's]] [[IZombie (TV series)|''iZombie'']], ''Pretty Little Addict'' and in a recurring role on the fourth season of ''[[Falling Skies]]''.<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\" /><ref name=\"FALLING SKIES Scoop: Dakota Daulby Talks Reeducation Camps and Humanity\u2019s Survival in Season 4\">http://www.thetvaddict.com/2014/06/22/falling-skies-scoop-dakota-daulby-talks-reeducation-camps-and-humanitys-survival-in-season-4/</ref><ref name=\"Dakota Daulby Discusses His Role on Falling Skies\">{{cite web |url=http://thetelevixen.com/2014/06/dakota-daulby-discusses-his-role-on-falling-skies/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-05 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714133820/http://thetelevixen.com/2014/06/dakota-daulby-discusses-his-role-on-falling-skies/ |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref> Daulby portrays the ruthless Nazi-esque head of the Espheni brainwashing camps, Kent Matthews. On the show, he worked closely with [[Maxim Knight]], [[Noah Wyle]], [[Will Patton]], [[Doug Jones (actor)|Doug Jones]] and [[Colin Cunningham]].<ref name=\"INTERVIEW: Dakota Daulby on FALLING SKIES, BLACK FLY & SITTING ON THE EDGE OF MARLENE\">http://yvrshoots.com/2014/06/interview-dakota-daulby-on-falling-skies-black-fly-sitting-on-the-edge-of-marlene.html#.U7eBgePZ-6x</ref>\n\nIn early 2014, Daulby won the leading role in the Canadian horror thriller, ''Black Fly'', which was released at international film festivals in 2015.<ref name=\"INTERVIEW: Dakota Daulby on FALLING SKIES, BLACK FLY & SITTING ON THE EDGE OF MARLENE\" /><ref name=\"Dakota Daulby: Today's Notable Young Professional\">{{cite web |url=http://notable.ca/nationwide/young-professionals/Dakota-Daulby-Todays-Notable-Young-Professional/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-05 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707084202/http://notable.ca/nationwide/young-professionals/Dakota-Daulby-Todays-Notable-Young-Professional/ |archivedate=2014-07-07 |df= }}</ref> Daulby received a nomination at Leo Awards for \"Best Male Lead in a Motion Picture\" - losing to his Black Fly co-star Matthew MacCaull. In November 2015, Daulby was nominated for and won the [[ACTRA]] Union of BC Performers (UBCP) award for the best emerging performer for his role in ''Black Fly''.\n\nDaulby co-wrote, co-directed, and co-produced over 20 short and alternative media films with [[New Image College|New Image Entertainment]].<ref name=\"B.C.'s Dakota Daulby's a pretty good bad guy in Falling Skies\" /><ref name=\"Camille Sullivan and Michael Eklund bag the big prizes at UBCP/ATRA 2015 awards\">https://www.straight.com/blogra/573801/camille-sullivan-and-michael-eklund-bag-big-prizes-ubcpactra-awards</ref> In 2016, he had a guest starring role opposite Academy Award nominatee [[Djimon Hounsou]], in [[M. Night Shyamalan]]'s ''[[Wayward Pines]]''.<ref name=\"ACTOR DAKOTA DAULBY TALKS 'WAYWARD PINES' AND M. NIGHT SHYAMALAN\">https://thehudsucker.com/2016/07/06/actor-dakota-daulby-talks-wayward-pines-and-m-night-shyamalan/</ref> Daulby played Travis in the [[Luc Besson]] fantasy epic, [[Warrior's Gate]].<ref name=\"seat42f\">{{cite web|url=http://www.seat42f.com/exclusive-wayward-pines-scoop-shining-the-spotlight-on-dakota-daulby.html|access-date=2017-01-30|date=2016-07-05|title=EXCLUSIVE: WAYWARD PINES Scoop: Shining the Spotlight on Dakota Daulby|first1=Tiffany|last1=Vogt|website=seat42f.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Other projects ===\n\nDaulby was the co-creator of the Vancouver-based 72 horror film festival, The Phrike Filmfest - also acting as the shows official MC. He is highly involved in New Image College's community events, he hosted and appeared on such shows like ''[[Breakfast Television]]'', the Fair at the PNE, [[EP Daily|Electric Playground]] and Shaw Television.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Camp Goodtimes''\n| Max\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Why Does God Hate Me?''\n| Matthew\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Girl Fight]]''\n| Sophomore Boy #1 \n| TV Movie\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''The Woodcarver''\n| Matthew\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Mimi & Me''\n| Sam Vaughn\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Spooksville (TV series)|Spooksville]]''\n| Jerome Simone; 1 episode\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Falling Skies]]''\n| Kent Matthews; 5 episodes\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Sitting on the Edge of Marlene]]''\n| Drew